    "longBusinessSummary": "HACISCO Joint Stock Company engages in the construction of other civil engineering projects in Vietnam. It undertakes the construction of industrial works; waterway structures, such as waterways, ports and river structures, tourist ports, sluice gates, dams, and dikes; tunnels; and other non-building construction works, including outdoor sports facilities, as well as public utility projects, railway, and roads. The company is also involved in the wholesale of computers, peripheral devices, software, electrical machinery, equipment, and electrical materials; specialized design activities; installation of design activities; completion of construction work; site preparation; construction of various types of buildings; and architectural and related technical consultancy activities. In addition, it provides direct support services for railway and road transport, including management of roads, bridges, tunnels, parking lots, car garages, and bicycle/motorbike parking areas; and imports and exports goods. The company was formerly known as Ha Noi Post & Telecommunications Construction and Installation Joint Stock Company and changed its name to HACISCO Joint Stock Company in September 2011. The company was founded in 1996 is headquartered in Hanoi, Vietnam.",
